snippet.textDisplay:
Lovely video Chris, your dad seems to be a genuinely nice guy. Definitely a tear jerker.

One thing that I have to comment on as a first responder, is that your dad's seating position is really not good. I don't know if it is because he just got the car and did not have the time to really adjust it.
But he sits way too close to the steering wheel, and therefore to the airbag. You obviously know that the symbiosis of the seat belt and air bag expansion decide the outcome and level of injuries one sustains in a crash, and according to the seating position in the car he will be in the space of the airbag when it is still expanding instead of landing on the completed cushion that is the airbag.
And yes, manufacturers do a poor job accommodating all sizes when it comes to pedal length and seating position. Perhaps you can make a video on how to get your pedals lengthened :-).

Your dad asked, here is my answer: 1959 Corvette.

Thanks Chris!
